# Russian Verbs

2 types:
- first type: ending in ит (it)
- second type: ending in <whateverelse>т

## First Type Conjugation

Example: думат (to think)

I think     - я   дума(ю)
You think   - ты  дума(ешь)
He thinks   - он  дума(ет)
She thinks  - она дума(ет)
We think    - мы  дума(ем)
You think   - вы  дума(ете)
They think  - они дума(ют)


## Second Type Conjugation

Example : говорить (to speak)

I speak     - я   говорю
You speak   - ты  говоришь
He speak    - он  говорит
She speak   - она говорит
We speak    - мы  говорим
You speak   - вы  говорите
They speak  - они говорят


## Past

For the past we just add a л to the base of the verb.
But beware that past can change slightly if we
are woman or if we speak as multiple people.
Let's make some examples.

All past               - add л
Past if you are woman  - add ла
Past if you are plural - add ли 


я говорил  (i spoke)  (if i am a male)
я говорила (i spoke)  (if i am a wommn)

ты знал   (you knew) (if you are a male)
ты знала  (you knew) (if you are a female)

мы говорили (we spoke)
вы говорили (you (plural) spoke)
они говорили (they spoke)

## Future (imperfective)

The analogous of the imperfective future is like using "will"
in English.

We build the imperfective future just by using the conjugated быть 
verb + the inifniteve form of the verb we want to use.

Example:

я   буду    + infinite verb (e.g., говорить)
ты  будешь  + infinite verb
он  будет   + infinite verb
она будет   + infinite verb
мы  будем   + infinite verb
вы  будете  + infinite verb
они будут   + infinite verb
